def der2pem(der, text='PUBLIC'):
    # Convert the DER encoded key to PEM format
    pem_header = f"-----BEGIN {text} KEY-----\n"
    pem_footer = f"-----END {text} KEY-----\n"
    
    # Encode the DER data to base64
    pem_body = PEM.encode(der)
    
    # Combine the header, body, and footer
    pem = b''.join([b(pem_header), pem_body, b(pem_footer)])
    
    return pem
